''[[Buffy the Vampire Slayer]]'' is an American television series created by [[Joss Whedon]], which premiered on March 10, 1997. It concluded on May 20, 2003, after seven seasons with 144 episodes in total, plus an unaired pilot episode.

The first five seasons aired on [[The WB Television Network|The WB]], and in 2001, it transferred to the [[UPN]] for its final two seasons.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cesnur.org/2001/buffy_april01.htm|title='Buffy,' Moving to UPN, Tries to Be WB Slayer|accessdate=October 20, 2006|work=cesnur.org}}</ref> In the United Kingdom, the entire series aired on [[Sky1]] and [[BBC Two]], and on [[TV3 (Ireland)|TV3]] in Ireland. The story line is continued in comic book form in [[Buffy the Vampire Slayer Season Eight|Season 8]] and [[Buffy the Vampire Slayer Season Nine|Season 9]].

All seven seasons of the series are available on individual DVD box sets for Regions 1, 2 and 4. Two [[Buffy the Vampire Slayer DVDs#Collections|complete series collections]] (''The Chosen Collection'' and ''The Complete DVD Collection'') have been released separately for these regions.

